{panel:title=Atlassian Update – 8 October 2019|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ebf2f9 | titleBGColor=#ebf2f9 | bgColor=#ffffff}
Hi everyone,

In the time since this suggestion was last updated, Atlassian has adopted [Atlassian account|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/your-atlassian-account-976161169.html], which is a single identity shared across all Atlassian cloud products. We're closing this suggestion in favor of ID-6403, which will track the same capability across all of our cloud products.

Regards,
Dave Meyer
{panel}

I dont know how common a requirement this is, but there are many Jira instances that I use (j.a.com, j.os.com, j.ch.com) where I want email notifications when I am at work - and when I am working at home.

It would be really nice to have a comma seperated list of emails to add for the email field.

(I have a feeling that apart from validation, this would work seemlessly with the mailer....)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-3151].
